    "description": "Shield-shaped cope hood showing the Madonna and Child standing on a crescent within an oval, flanked by two angels on each side. The figures are embroidered in polychrome silks, while the entire background is filled with gold metallic yarns laid with couching stitches.",
    "justification": null,
    "gallery_text": "Since medieval times, the cope hood has been non-functional, seemingly maintained as part of liturgical vestments simply as another surface to adorn in splendor. Embroidery for costly vestments such as these would have been designed by a professional designer, most likely a painter, working in collaboration with professional guild embroiderers whose repertoire of stitches, including underside couching and or nu\u00e9, were perfectly suited to interpreting painterly effects of perspective, dimensionality, and shading.",
